post_text:
Graduation 2020

Part 1:
Graduation for the class of 2020 will be Saturday, May 30 at 1:00pm. This ceremony will be by invitation only. To meet state and local guidelines we must limit the number of guest to only those invited by our graduating seniors.

Part 2:
Following the ceremony at 1:45pm we are asking all members of the community that wish to participate to join us for a drive by parade to acknowledge and celebrate the class of 2020. Staff will be there to collect any cards or small gifts you may want to drop off. We only ask that you please do not show up before 1:45pm as the parking lot will be closed, follow the path, and do not exit your vehicle

Live Stream:
Every effort will be made to live stream part 1. If we are able a link will be available on the schools home page.

More information can be found on graduation on the school's website www.columbia206.com

post_text:
"Graduation 2020"

The school is working to check off the last couple of boxes for the state and our insurance to provide our seniors with a graduation ceremony. We hope to have details come out over the weekend. We know the date is coming up fast.

In the mean time we would like to let everyone know that if you have a card or gift for the seniors we have 3 places you can drop it off. Hunters Market, Fruitland Service, and of course, the school. All cards and gifts will be brought back to the school to be disinfected and given to the seniors after graduation. Please drop off any larger gifts to the school.

As you may already be aware, about 2 hours ago, Governor Jay Inslee has mandated closure of all K-12 schools in Washington. This situation is fluid at this time and we are still gathering all of the details. We will use social media and our Instant Alert system and maings to provide you details as we know more. Please remain patient as we roll this out. It is new for everybody and as always, the safety and well being of our students, staff and community are our number one priority!
Respectfully,
Columbia School

post_text:
We would like to thank our students and staff for their quick and orderly response to our threat today. The students handled everything great and because of their efforts the evacuation went quickly.

The staff worked hard and even organized a lunch off site as we had to evacuate right before lunch.

All but a few students have either been picked up by parents or taken home on regular bus routes by the time of this posting.

An all call should be sent out later today when it is safe to return to the school building.
